.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH lock 2m
.XI lock - "Pipe cursor position lock"
.SH NAME
lock \- Pipe cursor position lock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "lock Mode"
.sp
\fBk\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
This mode can only be used while an incremental pipe (started by
.Ht ipipe-shell-command 2 )
is running in the current buffer, denoted by the
.Ht pipe 2m
being set. When this mode is enabled  and \*(mE  buffer  cursor is at the same
location as the process shell cursor, the buffer cursor is automatically moved
with the shell cursor.
.PP
This mode is automatically enabled for a piped buffer.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht ipipe-shell-command 2 ,
.Ht pipe 2m .
.ad
.FH
